# Fluff Date: 2026-02-24 13:31:06
<overview>
<p>The Fox-class corvette was the first warship constructed by the Federated Commonwealth and the first new combat JumpShip produced by any Inner Sphere power in over two hundred years. Originally designated the RX-78 during its development phase, the class was renamed in honor of First Prince Hanse Davion following his death in 3052, two months before the keel-laying ceremony for the lead vessel. Produced at shipyards on Galax and Alarion, the Fox became a potent symbol of restored naval capability for both the Federated Suns and the Lyran Alliance, and it eventually grew into one of the most numerous warship classes fielded by any Successor State during the late thirty-first century. The class served with distinction through the FedCom Civil War, the Word of Blake Jihad, and beyond, earning a fearsome reputation that belied its relatively modest displacement.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>At 240,000 tons, the Fox was remarkably well armed and protected for a corvette, capable of outgunning Star League-era destroyers nearly three times its size. The hull carried 394.5 tons of improved ferro-aluminum armor, quadruple the protection of many comparable corvettes and a match for vessels of significantly greater displacement. This exceptional survivability gave the Fox a decisive edge against overconfident opponents who underestimated the small vessel's resilience.</p><p>The weapons suite combined ten NAC/10 naval autocannons with eight Barracuda capital missile launchers and eight Naval Lasers in 45 and 55 classes, providing a versatile response capability across all firing arcs. Anti-fighter defense relied on sixteen Large Pulse Lasers backed by six anti-missile systems and six machine guns for close-in protection. Five docking collars gave the Fox substantial DropShip escort capacity for a vessel of its size, making it an ideal command vessel for small strike forces. A lithium-fusion battery enabled consecutive interstellar jumps without recharging, a rare and expensive capability that proved essential for border patrol and raiding missions where rapid ingress and egress were critical. The design's primary concession was crew comfort, with four personnel assigned to each of twenty-six cabins and recreational facilities limited to a single small lounge and two mess halls.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The FCS Invincible was the lead vessel, with keels laid in 3052. The FCS Antrim and FCS Rostock served with Task Force Serpent during Operation Bulldog, engaging Clan Smoke Jaguar warships at the Battle of Huntress in March 3060, where the Rostock was destroyed. The FCS Intrepid served as Field Marshal Ardan Sortek's command ship during the FedCom Civil War. At the Battle of New Avalon in November 3066, the FCS Kentares activated its K-F drive alongside the Avalon-class cruiser FCS Alexander Davion, annihilating both vessels. The FSS Antrim and FSS Bryceland sacrificed themselves in October 3067, conducting suicidal ramming attacks against the Blakist Aegis-class cruiser WoBS Herald of Justice to defend New Avalon, with all crew posthumously recommended for the Diamond Sunburst. The LAS Katrina Steiner, the first Lyran-produced Fox, was commissioned in April 3060 at Alarion and served through the Jihad before being destroyed during Operation SCOUR at Terra. The FSS Admiral Michael Saille participated in the liberation of Terra but was critically damaged when its task force commander disobeyed orders, resulting in the loss of missile defense coverage. The officer was court-martialed and executed. The Admiral Michael Saille ultimately survived as the last Federated Suns warship into the ilClan era.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>Design work on the Fox began in mid-3050, with the vessel reaching its final configuration by late 3051. First Prince Hanse Davion personally approved the design and contracted Federated-Boeing Interstellar to produce the class at the Port Simon yards orbiting Galax. The prince's death in 3052 prompted the redesignation from RX-78 to Fox-class in his honor. Construction of the lead vessel proceeded steadily until mid-3055, when ComStar imposed an embargo on Rolls Royce-produced interplanetary engine components, causing a sixteen-month delay. Terrorist attacks against the Federated-Boeing facilities at Galax further disrupted the program, pushing the first launch to 3058.</p><p>Despite these setbacks, production expanded rapidly across multiple yards. Federated-Boeing's Port Simon facility at Galax served as the primary construction site for the Federated Suns, while the Lyran Alliance established a parallel production line at the Port Sydney Naval Shipyards on Alarion. Universal Air also contributed to the program at Galax. Over twenty Fox-class corvettes were ultimately produced between the two nations, making it one of the most numerous warship designs in the Inner Sphere.</p><p>The FedCom Civil War proved a crucible for the class. Multiple Fox corvettes fought on both sides of the conflict, with the Battle of New Avalon in November 3066 serving as the decisive naval engagement. The battle ended when one Fox activated its K-F drive in close proximity to an Avalon-class cruiser, destroying both vessels in an unprecedented act that shocked both factions and effectively ended the fighting. Twelve Fox corvettes survived the Civil War in Federated Suns service, while the Lyran Alliance retained four operational vessels with two more under construction.</p><p>The Word of Blake Jihad devastated the Fox fleet. Two corvettes sacrificed themselves in suicidal ramming attacks to destroy a Blakist cruiser at New Avalon in late 3067. The Galax shipyards fell to Blakist attack in 3069, with two more Fox corvettes lost defending the facility. Additional vessels were destroyed at Hesperus, Tharkad, and during the liberation of Terra. Some were captured by the Word of Blake and turned against their former allies. By the end of the Jihad, only four Fox corvettes remained across both nations. Attrition continued in subsequent decades until a single vessel remained as the last operational warship in the Federated Suns navy by the mid-thirty-second century.</p>
</history>

